<HEADLINE> Xinhua World News Summary at 1530 GMT, August 16 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA -- President Fidel Ramos today ordered a thorough
investigation into Friday's two separate sea tragedies in Manila
Bay and a central Philippine strait which led to the death of at
least 19 people.
</P>
<P>
In a hand written memorandum, Ramos directed Transportation and
Communications Secretary Arturo Enrile to conduct a thorough probe
into the two sea accidents, one in Manila Bay and the other in
Biliran Strait in the central
Philippines. (BC-Philippines-Ramos-Sea Tragedy)
</P>
<P>
NEW DELHI -- Krishan Kant was elected vice president of India
today.
</P>
<P>
Krishan Kant, governor of Andhra Pradesh, was supported jointly
by the ruling United Front and the Congress and won 441 votes
while his rival, Surjeet Singh Barnala, backed by the Bharatiya
Janata Party and its allies, the biggest opposition in the
country, secured 273 votes. (BC-India-New Vice President)
</P>
<P>
JAKARTA -- Indonesian President Soeharto said today that the
government will always pay great attention to the poverty
alleviation program under the presidential instruction for the
promotion of least-developed villages (IDT) program.
</P>
<P>
In his state address before the plenary session of the
parliament to mark the 52nd anniversary of the country's
independence on August 17, the president that the IDT program, now
entering its fourth year, is one of the country's high priority
programs. (BC-Indonesia-Poverty-Program)
</P>
<P>
MOSCOW -- The Mir's three-man crew left the space station
Friday to videotape the damaged exterior which was punctured in a
space collision seven weeks ago.
</P>
<P>
In preparation for a vital repair job, the two Russian
cosmonauts and their American colleague spent about 45 minutes
traveling round the orbiting station in a Soyuz spacecraft,
getting their first look at the damaged Spektr module, Itar-Tass
news agency said. (BC-Russia-Mir)
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- In a speedy trial, the Palestinian court in
Jericho today sentenced two Palestinians to life imprisonment for
murdering an Israeli taxi driver Friday.
</P>
<P>
Another 17-year-old Palestinian was sentenced to 15 years in
jail for his part in the murder. The three confessed killing the
taxi driver, 45-year-old Ben Baruch from Jerusalem, in an attempt
to steal his money and his white Mercedes-Benz
car. (BC-Israel-Palestine-Murder)
</P>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG -- South Africa will build a satellite launching
center in Overberg in Western Cape Province, a local daily
Saturday Star reported today.
</P>
<P>
Western Cape Province is set to become the "Cape Canaveral", a
U.S. aerospace base, in the Southern hemisphere, earning the
region upward of 106 million U.S. Dollars a year and creating
hundreds of hi-tech aerospace jobs, the report
said. (BC-S. Africa-satellite)
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Twenty-six militants of the outlawed Kurdish
Workers' Party (PKK) have been killed after being tracked down by
the Turkish security forces, an official statement said
today. (BC-Turkey-PKK)
</P>
<P>
SANAA -- All the 10 Italian tourists kidnaped by armed
tribesmen Thursday in Yemen have been set free, according to
Yemeni security sources.
</P>
<P>
The four Italian tourists who were kidnaped Thursday in the
city of Amran, 45 kilometers north of Sanaa were released Friday,
a security source said here Friday night.
</P>
<P>
He said that the other six Italian tourists who were abducted
Thursday in Abyan province, 490 kilometers south of Sanaa, were
also freed Friday. (BC-Yemen-Italy-Abduction) 
</P>
</TEXT>
