<HEADLINE> Pakistan Adheres to Neutral Policy on Afghan Issue: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani President Farooq
Leghari said today that his country adheres to a policy of strict
neutrality and non-interference in the internal affairs of
Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
As a neighboring country, "we have a vital stake in durable
peace and stability in the region," Leghari told Lukhdar Brahimi,
special envoy of the UN Secretary General on Afghanistan, who
called on him at the Presidential Palace here today.
</P>
<P>
Leghari said that Pakistan fully supports the peace efforts by
the United Nations aimed at bringing about harmony and
conciliation among the rival Afghan factions and restoring peace
and stability in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
He referred to the enormous economic benefit which would accrue
to the countries of the region through mega oil and gas pipeline
projects once peaceful conditions prevailed in Afghanistan.
</P>
<P>
He also spoke about Pakistan's efforts towards the
establishment of a broad-based government in Afghanistan which
took into account all ethnic groups in the country.
</P>
<P>
Brahimi said that the UN Secretary General was committed to
help the Afghan people in resolving their problems and restoring a
lasting peace in their country.
</P>
<P>
He hoped that serious efforts being made by the UN and Pakistan
would yield positive results.
</P>
<P>
Brahimi arrived here Friday morning on a two-week mission to
assess the Afghan situation for the UN's further actions for
restoration of peace in that country.  
</P>
</TEXT>
