<HEADLINE> South Africa Moves to World Cup Finals </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, August 16 (Xinhua) -- South Afirca beat Republic
of Congo 1-0 on Saturday to book a spot in the World Cup soccer
finals for the first time.
</P>
<P>
Phil Masinga scored at the 14th minute before a sellout crowd
of more than 80,000, including Deputy President Thabo Mbeki and
about 30 government ministers and deputies at FNB Stadium.
</P>
<P>
The two teams had been tied for first in Africa Group Three.
Republic of Congo's Red Devils won a contentious first-round
encounter 2-0 in April at Pointe-Noire, but the South African
defense was stifling and got its second straight shutout.
</P>
<P>
Saturday's 1-0 effectively gave South Africa a two-goal lead,
because a tie would also advance them for their better goal
differential than Republic of Congo. 
</P>
</TEXT>
