<HEADLINE> Russia Takes Fourth Gold Medal At Euro Championships </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Olga Brousnikina and Maria
Kisseleva won the title to the synchronised swimming pairs event
Saturday, giving Russia the fourth gold overall in the European
swimming championships in Seville, Spain.
</P>
<P>
The pair scored 99.160 points to beat French rivals Virginie
Dedieu and Myriam Lignot (97.040) and Italians Giada Ballan and
Serena Bianchi (95.760) into second and third place.
</P>
<P>
On Friday, Olga Sedakova easily retained her synchronised solo
title, Vera Iliyina retained her diving title ahead of compatriot
Irina Lashko and Alexi Akatiev won the 5km open water event ahead
of fellow Russian Evgueni Bezrouchenko.  
</P>
</TEXT>
