<HEADLINE> Middle East Business Briefs </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The following are the business
briefs from the Middle East countries:
</P>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkish Airlines (THY) has announced to increase the
price of domestic flights by 17.02 percent, local newspaper Daily
News said Friday.
</P>
<P>
This decision was announced on Thursday by the Istanbul-based
THY, the paper said, adding the new prices will be effective as
of September 1.
</P>
<P>
For example, an air ticket from Ankara to Istanbul, which had
an old price of 9.4 million Turkish lira (around 58 U.S. dollars)
will be sold for 10.8 million Turkish lira (around 67
U.S. dollars).
</P>
<P>
Summer is always a golden season in Turkey for both foreign and
home tourists who love sunny sea beaches. This is believed to be
main cause of the provisional increase of the price.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- A new airway will be inaugurated between Cairo and
Kuala Lumpur on October 6, as a result of Egyptian Prime Minister
Kamal El-Ganzouri's recent visit to Malaysia, according to the
latest issue of the Middle East Economic Weekly published here.
</P>
<P>
The report said the new airway will start with two weekly trips
with a stopover either in Dubai or Beirut, but there will be
direct flights after the route become established.
</P>
<P>
The aim of this new airway is to encourage trade between Egypt
and Malaysia and for tourism promotion, the report quoted Sayed
Ragab, assistant foreign minister for Asian affairs as saying.
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- The number of tourists visiting Egypt in the year
1996/97 ending last June increased by 15.2 percent compared to
that of the previous year to reach 4.1 million. The number of
tourist nights spent by those tourists also rose by 14 percent,
Egyptian Tourism Minister Mamdouh Al-Beltagui said.
</P>
<P>
The minister said in a report submitted to the Secretary of the
National Democratic Party that the tourists who come to Egypt
comprises groups from all over the world. He said the number of
tourists from Arab countries increased by 20.1 percent than that
of the previous year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
