<HEADLINE> AIDS Cases Soaring in Zimbabwe </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The AIDS epidemic continues to
take its toll in Zimbabwe with the total number of reported AIDS
cases reaching at 63,937 as of December 1996.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a youth ''AIDS Festival" here today, Gabriel
Machinga,Zimbabwean Minister of Education, Sport and Culture disclosed
that it was
estimated that cumulative AIDS cases since the end of December
1996 was four times that figure.
</P>
<P>
"The most affected age group are young people aged 20 to 30,"
he said, adding that the prevalence of the HIV infection which
causes AIDS was also increasing among youths of 15 to 19 years
old.
</P>
<P>
"The tragedy is that there is no prospect of finding a cure or
a vaccine in the near future, which leaves us with prevention as
the only weapon against STD(sexually-transmitted
diseases)/HIV/AIDS," the minister noted.
</P>
<P>
Machinga appealed for positive behavioral change to reduce the
risk of HIV infection.
</P>
<P>
"The temptation for youths to take risks and experiment with
lives and sometimes with drugs, alcohol and even with their
bodies, puts them at very high risk of infection with sexually
transmitted diseases," he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
