<HEADLINE> Speedy Economic Development in North China Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, August 17 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
Province is now the country's sixth largest comprehensive economic
power, owing to the speedy development growth in recent years.
</P>
<P>
The province generated more than 345 billion yuan in GDP in
1996, double the 1991 figure, with the annual growth rate
surpassing the national average and reaching 15.1 percent
averagely since 1992.
</P>
<P>
The province registered nearly 26 billion yuan in revenues in
1996, 2.9 times the 1991 figure, with the average annual growth
rate coming to 23.3 percent.
</P>
<P>
Since 1991, the province has enjoyed a good grain harvest
annually and had a record 27.9 billion kg of grain in 1996, which
has laid a good foundation for the development of local animal
husbandry.
</P>
<P>
The local output of meat as well as livestock and eggs in 1996
rose by 150 percent and 340 percent over the 1991 figure,
respectively. The province has led the country in its
vegetable-growing acreage.
</P>
<P>
Added industrial value in the province exceeded 146 billion
yuan in 1996, 2.4 times the 1991 total.
</P>
<P>
Local retail sales of consumer goods in 1996 were reported to
be 2.4 times the 1991 number. And the province had had nearly
5,000 markets by the end of last year. 
</P>
</TEXT>
