<HEADLINE> North China Province Opens Wider to World </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SHIJIAZHUANG, August 17 (Xinhua) -- North China's Hebei
Province has scored remarkable economic progress by taking
advantage of its favorable geographical conditions.
</P>
<P>
Adjacent to Bohai Bay, the province surrounds two of the
country's municipalities, the capital city of Beijing and north
China's largest port city of Tianjin. Its providential location
has encouraged Hebei to increase economic cooperation with
domestic and overseas partners.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, the province handled 3.46 billion US dollars of
exports, a 98.9 percent rise from the 1991 sum, and had 73.5
million US dollars in foreign exchange from local overseas
tourists, a 66.3 percent rise from the 1991 figure.
</P>
<P>
During the five years from 1992 to 1996, the province used 4.2
billion US dollars of foreign investment, 6.7 times the total it
had registered by 1991.
</P>
<P>
Hebei set up 6,459 overseas-funded enterprised during the
1992-1996 period, 9.6 times the figure for 1991. More than 2,570
of them are now operational.  
</P>
