<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Investment Increasing in Hainan Province </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HAIKOU, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Southernmost China's Hainan
Province introduced more than 100 million US dollars of pledged
investment from Hong Kong during the first half of this year, a 35
percent rise from the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
The spendings were used for 40 projects, helping bring the
local total of overseas-funded projects to 96 during the six
months. Thirteen of them involved an investment in excess of five
million US dollars each.
</P>
<P>
In the past ten years, nearly half of the overseas investment
in Hainan, or 2.5 billion US dollars, came from Hong Kong, and was
used to set up more than 5,000 local enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Nearly half of the overseas-funded projects added during the
January-June period, or 46, were involved in industrial production
and cost 140 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
An increasing number of foreign investors have a strong
interest in developing the local rich resources such as offshore
natural gas and petroleum, tropical agriculture, and tourism, and
in funding local hi-tech projects.  
</P>
</TEXT>
