<BODY>
<HEADLINE> New Political Culture Established in Pakistan: </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Pakistani Information Minister
Mushahid Hussain Sayed said here today the government has
established corruption-free political culture and scandal-free
administration besides ensuring economic stability over the past
six months.
</P>
<P>
"Now there is a new socio-political environment in the country
and high-level political corruption has been virtually
eliminated," Mushahid said when briefing journalists on the six
months performance of the government led by Prime Minister Nawaz
Sharif.
</P>
<P>
On the economic front, he said, the government has succeeded in
reviving the economy through indigenous policies within a short
span of six months.
</P>
<P>
The tax-free budget has led to an increase in foreign exchange
reserves from 300 million U.S. dollars to the current level of 1.5
billion dollars, he said.
</P>
<P>
The information minister also said that legislation has
provided for structural changes to ensure political stability and
strengthening the rule of law.
</P>
<P>
The removal of Article 58(2) B of the Constitution, which had
empowered the President to dismiss an elected government, has
eliminated one of the basic causes of political instability since
1985, he said.
</P>
<P>
Similarly, the anti-defection law has removed the possibility
of political opportunism which was one of the worst problems
affecting the Pakistani political culture, he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
