<HEADLINE> US Navy Helicopter Crashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ABU DHABI, August 17 (Xinhua) -- A U.S. Navy helicopter
crashed in the northern Gulf Saturday but all four crew members
were rescued, a radio in the United Arab Emirates reported today.
</P>
<P>
The helicopter crashed at approximately 2:30 p.m. local
time (1130GMT) in international waters in the northern Arabian
Gulf when it was conducting routine operations, the UAE's
Capital Radio quoted a statement by the U.S. Naval Central
Command in the Gulf as saying.
</P>
<P>
All four crew members aboard were rescued after the crash
with one of them being treated for minor injuries, the
statement said. An investigation into the cause of the crash
was under way.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. Navy is part of a multi-national force which checks
shipping in the Gulf to enforce a U.N. trade embargo imposed on
Iraq after its 1990 invasion of Kuwait.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. keeps about 20,000 troops in the Gulf, including
some 20 warships. 
</P>
