<HEADLINE> India to Launch Remote Satellite Next Month </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Indian Space research
Organization (ISRO) is planning to launch the Indian remote
sensing satellite (IRS) next month, Press Trust of India (PTI)
said here today.
</P>
<P>
With this launching of the IRS, India would not only acquire
the capability to launch operational satellite into middle earth
orbit, but also join a select band of countries which had that
capability, PTI quoted ISRO sources as saying.
</P>
<P>
During the Ninth Five-Year Plan period (1998-2002), the
capacity to use transponders is expected to increase 25 to 30
percent and rules are to be framed for providing transponders to
the private sector.  
</P>
