<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Malaysia Never Doubts China's Sincerity: Deputy PM </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia has never doubted
China's sincerity to be friendly with its neighbors although major
powers in the West think that Beijing is building up its strength
to control Asia, Malaysia's Deputy Prime Minister Anwar Ibrahim
said today.
</P>
<P>
Anwar made the statement when opening the eight-day Zheng He
Memorial Exhibition here today, which is jointly organized by the
Malaysian Chinese Cultural Society, MCA (Malaysian Chinese
Association) Cultural Bureau and Malaysia-China Friendship
Association.
</P>
<P>
Recounting Admiral Zheng He's historical journey to the region
some 500 years ago, Anwar said that although the admiral who
served during the Ming Dynasty had a large and strong armada,
China did not display even then any intention to conquer its
neighbors.
</P>
<P>
The Chinese approach was far in contrast to those of major
powers from the West at the time like the Portuguese, Dutch,
Spanish, French and English who sent their armada to the region
with the sole intention of conquering small countries, he said.
</P>
<P>
"It is an historical fact that Zheng He was certainly a greater
admiral with a more superior fleet ... coming to this region, the
Malay world and all over the world, to build relations and not
with the colonial arrogance but to build a lasting bond of
friendship," Anwar said.
</P>
<P>
The Malaysian leader said the trade ties with China and the
spirit of friendship fostered during the time of Emperor Yong Le
and the Sultan of Melaka (Malacca) were greatly appreciated by
Malaysia to these days and would remain as long as both countries
continued to cherish the spirit of understanding and tolerance.
</P>
<P>
Anwar said these events which occurred between 1405 and 1433
were not given prominence by historical writers. Instead, he said,
they presented Christopher Columbus as a great sailor when in fact
his vessel only measured 90 by 30 feet compared with Admiral Zheng
He's 400 by 150 feet.
</P>
<P>
"He (Zheng He) was the most renowned Chinese admiral with the
biggest sailing fleet in the world and he was also a Muslim.
</P>
<P>
"The journey of Zheng He makes us understand our own history.
There is a need for a reconstruction of our own history based on
our own world view," Anwar said.
</P>
<P>
He said the present younger generation knew Columbus better
than Admiral Zheng He because the Malaysian and Asian history was
influenced by Eurocentrics.
</P>
<P>
This historical perspective should be corrected so that people
in the region could be proud of the achievements of Admiral Zheng
He who according to historical facts had visited more countries
than Columbus, he said.
</P>
<P>
The exhibition will also be held in Melaka (August 26-27),
Johor Bahru (August 29-30), Pulau Pinang (September 3-9), Alor
Setar (September 6-7) and Terengganu (September 9-10).  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
