<HEADLINE> Project to Provide Winter Shelter for Animals in Tibet </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LHASA, August 17 (Xinhua) -- The local government in north
Tibet Autonomous Region will fund a 250 million yuan project
designed to help domestic animals survive the region's harsh
winters.
</P>
<P>
Grasslands in North Tibet are home to one third of Tibet's
livestock. But devastating winter snowstorms have resulted in a
high death toll of animals, costing the region millions of yuan a
year.
</P>
<P>
As part of the government effort to improve the well-being of
local Tibetans, the three-year project aims to build barns and
sheds to shelter the more than seven million animals in the region
from snowstorms and frigid temperatures.
</P>
<P>
Other work to be done includes the fencing-in of 60,000
hectares of pastureland to ensure feed supply for the animals in
winter, and the training of over 1,200 personnel in veterinary
medicine. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
