 least four rebels and wounding 11 others. Meanwhile, the release
said, four soldiers were killed and four others injured in the
fighting.
</P>
<P>
Saturday afternoon at Murunkan in the same district, government
troops in a cordon and search operation observed a group of rebels
and opened fire killing two of them. Later, troops recovered the
two dead bodies.
</P>
<P>
The two dead bodies were handed over to the ICRC group
(International Committee of the Red Cross) in Mannar last night,
the release added.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a war for a separate Tamil state in
the north and east of the island country since 1983.  
