<DATE_TIME> 1997-08-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indonesia Celebrates 52nd Independence Anniversary </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JAKARTA, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Indonesia today held a grand
ceremony to celebrate the 52nd anniversary of its independence
from centuries of Dutch colonial rule.
</P>
<P>
Some 3,000 people including government ministers and
high-ranking officials, army chiefs and officers, diplomats,
veteran fighters and other guests attended the ceremony at the
Presidential Palace.
</P>
<P>
The ceremony opened with the booming of field guns at 10:00
a.m. (local time), just the same time on August 17, 1945 when
Indonesia's first president Sukarno proclaimed the country's
independence.
</P>
<P>
The formal transfer of power from the Dutch, who had ruled
Indonesia for more than 350 years before three years of Japanese
occupation during the second world war, came only in 1949 after
intermittent and some heavy fighting between colonial troops and
the guerrillas led by Sukarno.
</P>
<P>
Tens of thousands of Indonesians were killed between 1945 and
1949 in fighting to oust the Dutch occupants.
</P>
<P>
After a flag-hosting ceremony, House Speaker Wahono re-read the
text of the independence proclamation.
</P>
<P>
In his state address Saturday at the parliament to mark the
independence anniversary, President Soeharto called on the whole
nation to pay respect to the sacrifices of the national heroes.
</P>
<P>
The president also urged the Indonesian people to work harder
so as to catch up with the progress made by neighboring countries.
</P>
<P>
He called on the people to continue preserving the fighting
spirit and the spirit of nationalists and unity.
</P>
<P>
The president said Indonesia has made remarkable achievements
in its economic construction in the past two decades with an
average annual economic growth of 7 percent.
</P>
<P>
In 1996, Indonesia's per capita income reached 1,155 U.S.
dollars, 16 times higher than the figure in 1969, he added.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
