<HEADLINE> Kafelnikov to Face Rafter in New Haven Tennis Final </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Top seed Yevgeny Kafelnikov
of Russia defeated former champion Petr Korda 6-4, 7-6 (7-4)
Saturday for a final showdown against Australian Patrick Rafter at
the Pilot Pen tennis tournament in New Haven on Saturday.
</P>
<P>
Rafter, the eighth seed, overcame the booming serves of
Britain's Greg Rusedski 7-5, 4-6, 6-3 in another semi-final match
of the day.
</P>
<P>
There was only one service break in the Kafelnikov-Korda match,
that coming in the very first game when the Czech double faulted
on the final point.
</P>
<P>
The match was basically a baseline duel with Korda, the
lefthander from the Czech Republic who was the titleholder in the
event in 1991, often in trouble because of unforced errors. He
double faulted nine times. Kafelnikov had no double faults.
</P>
<P>
Kafelnikov, who had come into the match with a 5-2 record
against Korda, was down set point for the only time at 5-6 in the
second set, but eventually took the game to force the tiebreaker.
</P>
<P>
In the breaker, Korda started with a double fault but pulled
even at 3-3 before backcourt errors cost him the match. Down 5-4,
Korda hit one return long, then hit one into the net to end the
match. 
</P>
</TEXT>
