<HEADLINE> Foreign Banks Do Well in Chinese Capital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Beijing, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Eleven foreign banks have set up
branches in Beijing since the Chinese capital opened to overseas
financial institutions two years ago.
</P>
<P>
Total capital assets of these foreign bank branches have
reached 2.02 billion US dollars by the end of June, an increase of
120 percent on a year-by-year basis.
</P>
<P>
The deposits they attracted totalled 400 million dollars and
their accumulative loans amounted to 850 million dollars, up 48
percent and 230 percent respectively over the corresponding period
of last year, according to statistics released by the People's
Bank of China Beijing Branch.
</P>
<P>
Five foreign banks are reported to begin netting profits,
a sign of smooth operation and rosy business prospects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
