<HEADLINE> Show of Tibetan Culture Welcomed in Italy </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, August 16 (Xinhua) -- The brilliant performance of
China's Tibetan artists has been warmly welcomed at Italy's Aviano
International Folk Arts Festival.
</P>
<P>
The Tibetan artists presented five performances between August
9 and 15 in Aviano, a city in northern Italy.
</P>
<P>
Some audience said they were previously told that Tibetan
culture had been destroyed, but the allegation was proved to be a
lie after they watched the performances.
</P>
<P>
The Tibetan delegation also held an exhibition on photos,
musical instruments and costumes.
</P>
<P>
The Tibetan artists ended their performances today in Italy and
left for Switzerland's Fribourg to attend another art festival
there. 
</P>
