<HEADLINE> Venezuela's International Reserves Increase Sharply </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, August 16 (Xinhua) -- Venezuela's international
reserves increased 12.9 percent in five days from August 7 to 11,
the Central Bank announced.
</P>
<P>
In the five days, the reserves grew more than 2 billion
U.S. dollars from 16.34 billion to 18.5 billion, said the Central
Bank.
</P>
