<TEXT>
<P>
SHENZHEN, August 17 (Xinhua) -- Shenzhen, in Guangdong
province, is working on adding culture to its modern skyscrapers
and rushing cars, drawning up a blueprint for cultural development
for the decade.
</P>
<P>
There are ambitious plans for a number of massive cultural
facilities, because cultural development didn't match economic
growth in this special economic zone yet, according to Dong
Xiaoming, vice director of the Shenzhen Cultural Bureau.
